The paper deals with risk assessment and planning for autonomous driving, which is a topic closely related to robotics (cs.RO). The proposed algorithm involves tracking and predicting trajectories of other agents, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions using low-level commands, such as throttle, which suggests a focus on control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the evaluation of the proposed method involves comparing it to other algorithms, which is a common practice in machine learning (cs.LG).
